{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ConnectionClosed","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is returned as soon as the close handshake is finished (we have both sent and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"received a close frame) on the server end and as soon as the server has closed the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"underlying connection if this endpoint is a client."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Thus when you receive this, it is safe to drop the underlying connection."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Receiving this error means that the WebSocket object is not usable anymore and the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"only meaningful action with it is dropping it."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/liveviewnativecore\/websocketerror\/connectionclosed"]}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"WebSocket connection closed normally. This informs you of the close.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It’s not an error as such and nothing wrong happened."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"sections":[],"metadata":{"title":"WebSocketError.ConnectionClosed","modules":[{"name":"LiveViewNativeCore"}],"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:18LiveViewNativeCore14WebSocketErrorO16ConnectionClosedyA2CmF","roleHeading":"Case","symbolKind":"case","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ConnectionClosed","kind":"identifier"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/liveview-native-core.LiveViewNativeCore\/documentatio